# GitHub Pages Deployment Guide

## Deployment Workflow
The project uses GitHub Actions for automatic deployment to GitHub Pages.

### Build Process
1. `npm run build` - Builds the project using Gulp
2. Files are compiled from `src/` to `build/` directory
3. GitHub Actions automatically deploys `build/` contents to `gh-pages` branch
4. GitHub Pages serves from `gh-pages` branch root

### Manual Deployment
- `npm run deploy` - Manual deployment using gh-pages package
- `npm run build` - Build only (for testing)

### Key Configuration
- Build output directory: `./build`
- GitHub Pages source: `gh-pages` branch
- Node.js version: 18 (specified in workflow)
- Package manager: npm with `npm ci` for faster installs

### Workflow Triggers
- Automatic: Push to `main` or `master` branch
- Manual: `workflow_dispatch` event in GitHub Actions

### Site URL
- Production: https://georgiysergeev.github.io/time-spot--store/
